Sure! Here’s a simple test code for the ESP32 that blinks an LED connected to pin 2:

```cpp
void setup() {
  pinMode(2, OUTPUT); // Set pin 2 as an output
}

void loop() {
  digitalWrite(2, HIGH); // Turn the LED on
  delay(1000);           // Wait for 1 second
  digitalWrite(2, LOW);  // Turn the LED off
  delay(1000);           // Wait for 1 second
}
```

This code will blink the LED on and off every second. If you need further explanation or modifications, just let me know!
